sect1.sect2:
Introduction à Samba
The Samba package provides file et print services to SMB/CIFS clients et Windows networking to Linux clients. Samba can also be configured as a Windows NT 4.0 Domain Controller replacement (with caveats working with NT PDC's et BDC's), a file/print server acting as a member of a Windows NT 4.0 or Active Directory domain et a NetBIOS (rfc1001/1002) nameserver (which amongst other things provides LAN browsing support).
&lfs72_checked;
